  "texts": [
    "Secondly, the RoBERTa model boasts a greater number of parameters compared to the BERT model.",
    "This larger parameter space could provide more capacity for RoB-ERTa to learn intricate representations and patterns from the data, contributing to its superior performance.",
    "The third point of differentiation lies in the pre-training tasks.",
    "Specifically, RoBERTa omits the NSP task, which has been found to be non-essential, or even potentially counterproductive, in downstream tasks such as question-answering systems.",
    "This modification is likely to free up model's capacity for learning more beneficial representations."
  ],
